article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 42, St. Francis, Pa. 15
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- David Sinisi ran for four touchdowns and a school-record 247 yards on 32 carries as Monmouth routed St. Francis 42-15 on Saturday. Brett Burke also had a big day for the Hawks (3-3, 2-0 in Northeast Conference), throwing two touchdown passes and completing 17-of-22 for 147 yards. The Red Flash (0-5, 0-2) were led by George Little, who completed 32-of-58 passes for 322 yards and scored on a 1-yard run. Monmouth took control of the game early on as Sinisi scored on runs of 1 and 10 yards in the first quarter. Little's score with 2:39 left in the second quarter narrowed the lead to 14-6, but the Hawks quickly responded with a six-play, 74-yard drive that culminated in another 10-yard scoring run by Sinisi. The teams then traded scores in the third quarter. St. Francis' first drive ended with Zak Campbell's 20-yard field goal, but Burke hit Nick Romeo with a 6-yard touchdown pass to give Monmouth a 28-9 lead. The Red Flash responded on Omar Winston's 11-yard touchdown run, but Sinisi then got his final score on a 6-yard run. Burke concluded the scoring with a 2-yard pass to Rodney Salomon late in the fourth quarter.
